Description: Fragment of pottery transport amphora. Flattened handle, curving. Rectangular stamp with rounded ends. Clay fine cream-buff; pink core.
Curator's comments: Petrie draw two such stamps (EES XVII p.110, 23 and 133, 7). The clay is much lighter than other pieces with similar stamps.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1223)
